Datathons are a competition for data-driven, analytically minded students. This competition challenges students from the world's best universities to tackle real-world social challenges in topics like urban traffic, renewable energy, education, and more - all while competing to win $25,000 in cash prizes and interviews for internship and full-time positions at Citadel. The winning team of the competition will also receive the chance to represent their school against other top-tier universities in the Data Open Championship, a grand finale Datathon event in the Spring of 2021, and win a $100,000 cash prize.

If you are curious to see what a Datathon looks like, we encourage you to check out these videos from our past events:
Dublin Datathon: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F0nQJcB8rhI&amp;
2017 Datathon series finale held at the New York Stock Exchange: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LPZ-bbAdwJE&amp;

The Summer Invitational Datathon is hosted by Citadel LLC &amp; Citadel Securities in partnership with Correlation One. Participants will be able to work remotely on their submissions during the week of July 13, on their own schedule. The winners will be announced on Monday, July 20th in the Awards Ceremony Webinar.

Sign up at www.thedataopen.com to complete the registration questionnaire and assessment before the deadline on Thursday, July 9th!
